descript.abstract: This point dataset contains spot height values across Horse Cave, KY.
descript.purpose: This data is derived from terrain models constructed from USGS DLG Hypsography data. It is intended to be used to demonstrate the construction of a TIN surface using various vector data sources.

srcinfo.srccontr: Data was derived from a terrain model created from DLG source data.

procstep.procdesc: The DLG data was converted to shapefile in ArcMap. The data was converted to a TIN, then to raster and resampled, then to TIN with loose vertical accuracy, and then significant nodes were extracted in ArcInfo for spot heights. Some of these nodes were removed in ArcMap to futher reduce the size/disk overhead of the data.

attracc.attraccr: The spot heights were derived from a generalized terrain model constructed from USGS DLG data. The model was simplified in order to reduce the size of the dataset.
